A wata ganawar da za a yi da shi, Trump zai gabatar da dan takarar kotun koli Brett Kavanaugh, wanda a 'yan kwanakin nan ya shiga cikin wata takaddama game da cin zarafin mata da FBI ke bincike.
Amma babban burin jam'iyyar Republican a wannan taron shi ne samun wasu 'yan takara masu karfin gwiwa a zaben da za a yi a watan Nuwamba.
A cewar ofishin yakin neman zaben Trump, ganawar biyar masu zuwa za ta kasance ne domin "tabbatar da aiki da kuma karfafa goyon baya yayin da 'yan Republican ke kokarin kare masu rinjaye da karfafa su a majalisar dattijai da majalisar wakilai", in ji Reuters.
"Samun iko da majalisar dokoki yana da matukar muhimmanci yayin da shugaban ke shirin ziyartar jihohi da dama a lokacin yakin neman zabe", in ji wani kakakin yakin neman zaben Trump wanda ya musanta cewa sunansa Reuters ne.
A cewar West Virginia Metro News, wannan taron, wanda za a yi a filin wasa na West Bank a Willingdon, na iya janye magoya baya daga "Ohio da Pennsylvania, kuma za a ba da rahoto ga kafofin watsa labarai na Pittsburgh".
A ranar Laraba da ta gabata, Trump ya sake ziyarar jihar West Virginia, jihar da ya lashe zaben da kashi 40 cikin 100 a 2016.
Trump yana neman goyon bayan dan takarar Sanata na Jam'iyyar Republican na West Virginia, Patrick Morris, wanda sakamakonsa ya yi ta yaduwa a cikin binciken.
"Ba alama ce mai kyau ba ga Morrissey lokacin da shugaban ya je wurinsa don samun goyon baya", in ji Simon Heather, masanin kimiyyar siyasa a Jami'ar West Virginia, a cewar Reuters.
