Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da 'tallace-tallace na farfaganda' da 'ta'addanci'
Mako guda bayan da wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani talla mai shafi hudu da ke neman Amurka ta ba da tallafi a kan cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka wajen yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana a ranar Laraba da ta gabata game da wani karin farashin China Daily a cikin Des Moines Register - jaridar da aka fi siyarwa a jihar Iowa - bayan zargin China da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka na 6 ga Nuwamba, wanda China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka, wanda ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka fadawa Reuters, ya zama wani sabon mataki a yakin da Washington ke yi na matsa lamba kan kasar Sin.
Duk da cewa al'ada ce ga gwamnatocin kasashen waje su sanya tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, a halin yanzu Beijing da Washington suna cikin yakin cinikayya inda suke kara haraji kan kayayyakin da suke shigowa da juna.
An tsara takunkumin da China ta yi a farkon yakin cinikayya don kawo wa masu fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, masana kasar Sin da Amurka sun ce.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa na dogon lokaci, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona a kasar Sin, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da 'yan kasuwa.
A cikin jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Litinin, Branstad ya rubuta cewa China "yana ninka wannan tashin hankali ta hanyar yada farfaganda a cikin 'yan jaridarmu".
"A cikin yada farfaganda, gwamnatin kasar Sin tana amfani da al'adun Amurka na kyauta na magana da 'yanci na jarida ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A bambanci, a nan a cikin wata jarida a titin Beijing, za ku ga iyakancewar bambancin ra'ayi kuma ba za ku ga ainihin bambancin ra'ayi da jama'ar kasar Sin za su iya yi game da yanayin tattalin arzikin kasar Sin ba, wanda ya nuna cewa kafofin watsa labarai suna karkashin kulawar jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa "wani daga cikin manyan jaridu a kasar Sin ya ki buga" labarinsa, amma bai ce wane jarida ba.
Bayan da aka yi wa Kavanaugh rashin nasara, 'yan Republican sun fi jin tsoron mata kafin zaben fidda gwani, masu sharhi sun yi gargadin.
Yayin da manyan 'yan Republican ke jiran kare dan takarar kotun koli Brett Kavanaugh kan wasu zarge-zargen cin zarafin mata, manazarta sun yi gargadin cewa za su sha wahala a zaben tsakiyar shekara, musamman daga mata.
A game da wannan motsin zuciyarmu ya kasance musamman high, kuma mafi yawan Republicans riga rajista da kuma ji cewa suna so su matsa zuwa ga zabe.
"Ba za a iya yin watsi da wannan ba", in ji Grant Rieher, farfesa a fannin siyasa a Makarantar Maxwell a Jami'ar Syracuse, a wata kasida da aka buga a ranar Asabar.
Riheerer ya ce yana shakkar cewa matakin da Sanata Jeff Flake na Arizona ya dauka a lokacin da ya gabata na neman a binciki FBI zai isa ya kwantar da hankalin masu jefa kuri'a.
"Mata ba za su manta da abin da ya faru jiya ba - ba za su manta ba gobe ko a watan Nuwamba", in ji Karin Jean-Pierre, babban mai ba da shawara da kuma mai magana da yawun ƙasa na ƙungiyar ci gaba ta MoveOn a ranar Juma'a, a cewar jaridar Washington.
A ranar Juma'a da safe, masu zanga-zangar a majalisar dattijai sun yi ta rera waka "Nuwamba tana zuwa!" lokacin da 'yan Republican da ke kula da kwamitin shari'a suka yanke shawarar ci gaba da nadin Kavanaugh duk da shaidar Dr. Christine Blaise Ford, in ji Mic.
"Democrat za su kasance masu himma da himma sosai", in ji Steve Rosenberg, wani mai nazarin siyasa na jam'iyya.
"Mutane suna cewa ya riga ya yi girma; gaskiya ne.
Amma zai iya zama mafi girma, musamman ma tsakanin mata masu jefa kuri'a a cikin unguwannin karkara da kuma tsakanin matasa masu jefa kuri'a, tsakanin shekaru 18 zuwa 29, waɗanda ko da yake ba sa son shugaban kasa, ba sa yawan shiga cikin zaben".
Ko da bayan shaidar Ford a fili game da zargin cin zarafin wani dan takarar kotun koli, manazarta sun ce zai yi mummunan sakamako idan 'yan Republican suka ci gaba da shaida.
"Wannan ya zama abin takaici ga 'yan Republican", in ji Michael Steele, tsohon shugaban kwamitin Republican na kasa, a farkon makon da ya gabata, kamar yadda NBC News ta ruwaito.
"Ba wai kawai batun zaben kwamitin bane, ko kuma zaben karshe, ko kuma sanya Kavanaugh a kujerar, amma kuma yadda 'yan Republican suka bi da shi da kuma yadda suka bi da shi", in ji Guy Cecil, darektan fifiko na Amurka, wata kungiya da ke tallafawa zaben 'yan Democrat, a cewar wani gidan rediyon.
Amma jama'ar Amirka suna da ɗan shakku game da wanda za su amince da shi a cikin shaidar Ford da Kavanaugh, kuma suna goyon bayan Kavanaugh.
Wani sabon bincike da YouGov ya yi ya nuna cewa kashi 41 cikin ɗari na masu amsa sun gaskata ko kuma sun yi imani da shaidar Ford, yayin da kashi 35 suka ce sun yi imani ko kuma sun yi imani da Kavanaugh.
Bugu da ƙari, kashi 38 cikin ɗari sun ce Kawano ya yi kuskure ko kuma ya yi kuskure a lokacin da yake ba da shaida, yayin da kashi 30 cikin ɗari suka ce Ford ya yi kuskure.
Bayan matsin lamba daga Flake, FBI na yanzu tana binciken Ford, kamar yadda ake tuhumar akalla daya daga cikin masu gabatar da kara, Deborah Ramirez, in ji Guardian.
